<text>Using radio buttons in HTML text box

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;


A group of radio buttons can be created using the following lines of code:

&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;group name&quot; uid=&quot;uid1&quot; value=&quot;text1&quot; script=&quot;s1&quot; alt=&quot;tip1&quot; selfscript=&quot;ss1&quot; checked&gt;
&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;group name&quot; uid=&quot;uid2&quot; value=&quot;text2&quot; script=&quot;s2&quot; alt=&quot;tip2&quot; selfscript=&quot;ss2&quot; enabled=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;group name&quot; uid=&quot;uid3&quot; value=&quot;text3&quot; script=&quot;s3&quot; alt=&quot;tip3&quot; selfscript=&quot;ss3&quot;&gt;

 
Important: Do not enclose the embedded HTML components within &lt;form&gt; tags:

&lt;FORM action=&quot;blah&quot; method=&quot;post&quot;&gt;
&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;group name&quot; uid=&quot;uid1&quot; value=&quot;text1&quot; script=&quot;scripts1&quot; selfscript=&quot;selfscripts1&quot; alt=&quot;tooltip1&quot;&gt;
&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;group name&quot; uid=&quot;uid2&quot; value=&quot;text2&quot; script=&quot;scripts2&quot; selfscript=&quot;selfscripts2&quot; alt=&quot;tooltip2&quot;&gt;
&lt;/FORM&gt;

If you do so, MW will try to send the data to a server, instead of a model.
 

For the radio buttons to be in the same group (i.e. a mutually exclusive mode in which only one radio button can be selected at a time), they must have the same name attribute. The following is an example of using HTML radio buttons:

  
To view the source, save this page to your disk, enter the authoring mode and right-click (or CTRL+click on Mac OS X without a multiple-button mouse) on the text box.

&#12304;This is an embedded model container.&#12305;

Unlike buttons, the value attributes are not used as text of radio buttons. Therefore, you have to write text next to a radio button.

